{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"a3228fc0-4ecc-49c4-b19d-4174718e2e35","content":"Here's the equivalent command for Microsoft.Testing.Platform on .NET 8:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test \\\n  --filter \"Category=Integration\" \\\n  -- \\\n  --report-trx \\\n  --coverage \\\n  --coverage-output-format cobertura \\\n  --crashdump \\\n  --hangdump \\\n  --hangdump-timeout 5m\n```\n\n**Key changes:**\n| VSTest flag | MTP equivalent |\n|---|---|\n| `--logger trx` | `--report-trx` |\n| `--collect \"Code Coverage;Format=cobertura\"` | `--coverage --coverage-output-format cobertura` |\n| `--blame-crash` | `--crashdump` |\n| `--blame-hang` | `--hangdump` |\n| `--blame-hang-timeout 5m` | `--hangdump-timeout 5m` |\n\n**Prerequisites** — add these NuGet packages and the MSBuild property:\n\n```xml\n<!-- Directory.Build.props or your .csproj -->\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n</PropertyGroup>\n\n<ItemGroup>\n  <PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.TrxReport\" />\n  <PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CodeCoverage\" />\n  <PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CrashDump\" />\n  <PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.HangDump\" />\n</ItemGroup>\n```\n\n`--filter` stays before `--`; all MTP-specific flags go after it.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"d32178e9-e295-4e05-b7c9-58428bbe8858","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating their CI test command from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP) on .NET 8. Let me provide the equivalent command.\n\nKey differences between VSTest and MTP:\n- `--filter` → `--filter` (same)\n- `--logger trx` → `--report-trx` (MTP built-in)\n- `--collect \"Code Coverage;Format=cobertura\"` → `--collect-coverage` with `--coverage-output-format cobertura` (using Microsoft.CodeCoverage)\n- `--blame-crash` → `--crashdump` (MTP built-in)\n\n\n- `--blame-hang` → `--hangdump` (MTP built-in)\n- `--blame-hang-timeout 5m` → `--hangdump-timeout 5m`\n\nWith Microsoft.Testing.Platform, the command structure changes depending on how you invoke it. On .NET 8, you'd use `dotnet test` with `--` to pass MTP-specific arguments, though the exact syntax varies between versions.\n\nActually, I need to clarify this. With .NET 8 and MTP, `dotnet test` still defaults to the VSTest runner unless you explicitly enable MTP support in the project file or run the test executable directly. You can set `<TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>` to make `dotnet test` use MTP, or just run the compiled test executable with the MTP flags directly.\n\nThe flag mappings between VSTest and MTP are slightly different — filters work the same way, but logging and coverage collection use different syntax. For example, `--report-trx` replaces `--logger trx`, and coverage uses `--coverage` with format options. The blame-related flags also map to dump options like `--crashdump` and `--hangdump`, though I'm still working through the exact timeout syntax for hang dumps. Clarifying the MTP integration with `dotnet test` on .NET 8—I need to distinguish which arguments go before the `--` separator and which go after, since `dotnet test` recognizes some flags like `--filter` directly while MTP-specific options come after the delimiter. I'll provide a clear summary of the testing setup with the command and required packages.","outputTokens":1735,"requestId":"4C1C:24E49D:D4C0F0:1091365:6A012A02"},"id":"15a9eea9-dc74-47ab-be96-2810c3481d2b","timestamp":"2026-05-11T01:00:13.454Z","parentId":"c9bf4ecc-3e0b-4ba3-9309-028fdf61e583"}
